<p><i><b>Sophie's World</b></i> (<i><b>Sofies verden</b></i> in the original <a href="/wiki/Norwegian_language" title="Norwegian language">Norwegian</a>) is a <a href="/wiki/Novel" title="Novel">novel</a> by <a href="/wiki/Jostein_Gaarder" title="Jostein Gaarder">Jostein Gaarder</a>, published in 1991. It was originally written in Norwegian, but has since been translated into <a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a> (1995) and many other languages.</p>
<p>Mostly consisting of <a href="/wiki/Dialogue" title="Dialogue">dialogues</a> between Sophie Amundsen and a mysterious man named Alberto Knox, interwoven with an increasingly bizarre and mysterious plot, <i>Sophie's World</i> acts as both a novel and a basic guide to <a href="/wiki/Philosophy" title="Philosophy">philosophy</a>.</p>
